cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CE, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the use of the World Wide Web for social mobilization, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and cyber security (cs.CYBER). The paper also discusses the use of incentives and mechanisms for information dissemination, which falls under the categories of computational engineering (cs.CE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper analyzes the theoretical and practical properties of the mechanism used, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI).
